annotation.TEXT: It's quite interesting what the music sounds like while sped up like this. (Along with some other sound effects!)
Bye, Yoshi!
Careful! Wouldn't want to make a stupid mistake now!
And, as if that wasn't abusive enough...
Plenty of shells available here, but I will only need one.
Reload!
Now, in this level, there is a koopa shell later on, but using a Bob-omb is much quicker. In addition, after being taken through a pipe, it will never explode on me, so that's nice!
Now let's play a bonus game that doesn't rely so much on luck!
That's it! I can't go on like this anymore!
Yeah, that was mean. But still funny!
At least I finally managed to pull it off after a few dozen tries, and this is the last tricky 1-up chamber!
And now to enter the final level, slooowwwly...
<- Shoot off the side of the screen! ->
Got one this time, but...
Since there are shells available, I gotta take one with me.
Hi, Yoshi!
Honestly, I think the ice block is worse than just using my head. I'm no luckier with it, and it's easy to break it by accident!
STATE 0 SAVED.
I'm showing this part at normal speed, because... Well, you'll see.
Alright! I'm done here! Let's finish the level!
BGM: The Melancholy of Haruhi Suzumiya - Koi No Mikuru Densetsu
Thank you! I was starting to get sick of this Tetris music! (If you want a taste of what this was actually like, stick around at the end of the video!)
SMW challenge by mwilson90: In each of the nine five-tiered 1-up chambers, collect all five 1-ups, then finish the level.
148 axnillion attempts later... (Okay, now I'm just making up numbers!)
Okay, just one more! Oh, please give it to me...
This would be easier with the Yellow Switch active, but I can still get in no problem!
Death BGM: Castlevania - Lost Life
Okay, I'm one-third done with this challenge!
Now, there are shells later in the level, but I'm going to go with a P-switch this time, just for variety.

However, I discovered a trick with carriable objects that evens the odds a bit! As you can see, by cape-spinning this shell so that it hits the blocks, I'm guaranteed success! (At least, I've never seen this fail yet!)
One level done. Eight more to go.
Once again, I forget what I'm doing for the first block, but still get lucky!
Yep, even now, stupid mistakes are still present. Fortunately, none of them are fatal.
BGM: Balloon Fight - Balloon Trip
Hi, Yoshi!
6 attempts later... (Yeah, this one didn't take a ton of tries!)
Argh! Yeah, I've messed up that way a few times, too!
No, it's not kidding, but at least next time I'll enter the bonus game no matter what number I get (assuming I don't miss entirely)!
Now, because of how luck-based this mission is, I've placed savestates at the beginning of each 1-up chamber. It's just downright unfair otherwise!
Seriously?! I got 1? You're kidding, right?
For some reason, I had more luck with the P-switch than I expected. Maybe it's because of how I was throwing it to hit two blocks at once, but I don't know...
Hi, err... Bye, Yoshi!
Okay, I'm doing good here!
BGM: Ducktales - The Moon
Ooh, maybe I can make it this time?
Another whoops! I missed and hit the block above instead, but once again, I got lucky!

Also, I'm not allowed to cape-spin the sides of the blocks, and if there are any carriable objects in the level that I can hit the blocks with, I must use one. Otherwise, just hit the blocks with my head.
YES!!! That took forever! Now for the rest of the level!
Two levels left!
Also, in case you didn't already know this, the third block in every row is guaranteed to produce a 1-up if you got coins from the other two, so no special tricks are needed for them!
Whoops! Almost forgot to bring an ice block with me!
Reload!
And in these annoying levels, it generally went on like this for a few dozen attempts, until the RNG finally decided to give me a break!
If this did start taking me a ton of tries, though, I would've definitely gone with a shell instead!

annotation.author: SomeGuy712x
annotation.TEXT: Now that's a close call!
Whoa! Be careful with that shell!
Now, in this level, the only carriable objects I'm aware of are ice blocks. Fortunately, they won't melt after being taken through a pipe, but that's the only good thing.
Crap! I thought I had something this time!
Oops! Well... Bye, Yoshi!
Once again, no carriable objects. This isn't going to be good...
Fail. Gotta reload.
Come on! Just one more!
I'm going to speed up most of the video outside of the 1-up chambers, just to save time. This is why the main parts of the levels don't have custom music.
D'oh!!!
BGM: Mother/Earthbound - New Age Retro Hippie
Fail again. Reload!
And that's a wrap here, but the next level's 1-up chamber won't be so easy!
BGM: Tetris (Tengen) - Karinka
BGM: Tetris GB - Type C
However, not all levels have an object that can be used this way. I'll be getting to them later.
Nuts! Reload!
259 attempts later... (Okay, I'm exaggerating, but it still took a lot of tries!)
BGM: Tetris GB - Type A
NOOOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!!!!
37 attempts later... (Or some number around there... I wasn't keeping exact count.)
I can still use the cape for other stuff, though. So let's get to the first 1-up chamber!
Just one more! Come on!
...and then rapidly speed through it! Also, I don't have to worry about finding a shell (though there are plenty available), as there is a koopa placed right on top of the 1-up chamber pipe!
Here goes...
Now, I'm replaying one of the more annoying levels, just so you can see, and hear, what multiple failures in a row was sort of like.
Oh, look at that! I managed to hang onto Yoshi at the goal this time! Too bad he's of no use in the 1-up chambers, so I'll have to get rid of him at some point.
BGM: Arcana - Draven's Valley Pass
BGM: Chrono Trigger - Corridors of Time
Now I have 98 stars, so if I hit the goal tape at anything other than 1, I'll enter the bonus game!
I'm more than halfway done now!
BGM: Yoshi's Cookie - Battle Theme C
Fortunately, I have no trouble with the rest of the level, but I would've been pissed if I somehow screwed up now!
This time, I'm not fooling around with the goal tape!
Whoops! For a second there, I forgot what I was doing. Fortunately, the first block gave me a coin anyway!
And that's it! All I have to do now is finish the level!
Whoo-hoo!!!
Okay, making progress...
This didn't always work, but throwing the P-switch in this manner seemed to increase my chances of success...
It would've been nice if I got 50, but whatever. And now, the challenge is complete!
0 attempts later... (I think...)
There's no carriable objects available this time, so I'll be using my head in this 1-up chamber.
BGM: Tetris NES/GB - Type B
